{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2016/12/24/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Bindings in Other Languages</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://riverbankcomputing.com/software/pyqt\">Python (via PyQt)</a> <a href=\"https://www.riverbankcomputing.com/software/pyqt/download5\">📦</a> - Arguably the most comprehensive and well-known binding of Qt to another language.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-24T21:31:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Third-Party Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.riverbankcomputing.com/software/sip\">SIP</a> <a href=\"https://www.riverbankcomputing.com/hg/sip\">📦</a> - Generates Python bindings for C or C++ libraries.  Has special support for Qt signals and slots, and was used to create <a href=\"https://riverbankcomputing.com/software/pyqt\">PyQt</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-24T21:25:22.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>New Functionality</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.devmachines.com/qtitanribbon-overview\">QtitanRibbon</a> - For fans of the ribbons that Microsoft uses in their software.  Commercial.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-24T21:20:02.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Official Tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://doc.qt.io/archives/vs-addin\">Qt Visual Studio Add-in</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/qt-labs/vstools\">:octocat:</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/qt-labs/vstools\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">20</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":20,\"repo\":\"qt-labs/vstools\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - If you'd rather stick to Visual Studio, this add-in will let you do that.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-24T21:19:19.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://planet.qt.io\">Planet Qt</a> - Official aggregation of first-party and third-party Qt-related blogs.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-24T20:38:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Books</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.packtpub.com/application-development/pyside-gui-application-development-second-edition\">PySide GUI Application Development - 2nd Edition</a>, by Gopinath Jaganmohan and Venkateshwaran Loganathan - Imagine these other books, but in Python.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-24T19:58:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Official Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.qt.io/newsletters\">Qt Newsletters</a> - The best of Qt, straight to your spam filter.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-24T18:35:47.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"JesseTG/awesome-qt","categoryHTML":"<h2>Blogs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog\">Woboq</a> - Another software consulting firm that also contributes code to Qt.  They seem to specialize in Qt's core architecture.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog/moc-myths.html\">Moc myths debunked</a> - The magic that Qt appears to rely in is really just a bunch of code generators.  This post will bring you up to speed on the reality of the <code>moc</code>, the most notable one.</li>\n<li>How Qt Signals and Slots Work [<a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog/how-qt-signals-slots-work.html\">1</a>, <a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog/how-qt-signals-slots-work-part2-qt5.html\">2</a>, <a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog/how-qt-signals-slots-work-part3-queuedconnection.html\">3</a>] - Qt's signals/slots system lets any object talk to any other object.  Understanding these three articles will help you take full advantage of the feature.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog/qmetatype-knows-your-types.html\">QMetaType knows your types</a> - C++ isn't known for having good run-time type information, so Qt brings its own.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog/cpp11-in-qt5.html\">C++11 in Qt5</a> - Stop writing C++ like it's 2003; learn how you can take advantage of recent C++ features in your Qt applications.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog/cpp14-in-qt.html\">C++14 for Qt programmers</a> - <code>s/2003/2011/</code></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog/qstringliteral.html\">QStringLiteral explained</a> - String literals are widely used in many applications; wouldn't it be nice if you could make them faster to access?</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://woboq.com/blog/nice-debug-output-with-qt.html\">Nicer debug output in Qt using QT_MESSAGE_PATTERN</a> - It's nice to be able to read your application's logs.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-12-24T18:30:29.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sfischer13/awesome-frege","categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries</h2><h3>Android</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mchav/froid\">froid</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mchav/froid\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-ri